                           <p style="clear: left;">
	<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;TEG events are open to all Dundee University, Abertay University and Dundee College students.</span><br>
                           <strong>1.a.</strong> Dundee University staff are free to attend all events except The Enterprise Challenge.<br>
	<strong> 1.b.</strong> Admission is subject to prior registration with TEG's website and the reservation of a place for the respective event.<br>
	<strong>1.c.</strong> The event capacity is set by the management team prior to the event depending on event nature and venue size and arrangements.</p>
		</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="panel panel-default">

                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>	<strong>2 </strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Reserved places must be claimed until 5 minutes prior to the scheduled start of the event.</span><br>
	<strong>2.a.</strong> If students fail to claim their place until 5 minutes prior to the scheduled start of the event they may lose it to other students who haven't made a reservation for the event.<br>
	<strong>2.b.</strong> If students know they will arrive late due to unavoidable circumstances they can inform the management team of this via email at least 2 hours prior to the scheduled start of the event and their places will be kept for them regardless of 2.a.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="panel panel-default">

                    <div class="panel-body">
                       <p>
	<strong>3.</strong> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Students who come to events having failed to register in advance may be admitted subject to having unreserved places available.</span><br>
            <strong>3.a.</strong> If all available places are filled students may be admitted 5 minutes prior to the scheduled start of the event and take the places of students who registered but failed to take their seats.<br>
	&nbsp;</p>
